Dirk Helbing - Wikipedia
snippet: Helbing received an honorary PhD from Delft University of Technology (TU Delft). Since June 2015 he was affiliate professor at the faculty of Technology, Policy and Management at TU Delft for some years, where he led the PhD school in "Engineering Social Technologies for a Responsible Digital Future". Dirk Helbing started out as a physicist.

title: Dirk Helbing
snippet: Dirk Helbing is Professor of Computational Social Science at the Department of Humanities, Social and Political Sciences and affiliate of the Computer Science Department at ETH Zurich. He earned a PhD in physics and was Managing Director of the Institute of Transport & Economics at Dresden University of Technology in Germany.

title: Dirk Helbing
snippet: Dirk Helbing worked as Managing Director of the Institute for Transport & Economics at TU Dresden and is now Professor of Sociology, in particular of Modeling and Simulation at ETH Zurich.
